    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `image-text-to-text` Pipeline\n\n### What was found in the codebase\n\n- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` **already exists** in `src/models.js` (line 8736), supporting 11 VLMs: LLaVA, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, Qwen2-VL, Florence2, Moondream, Idefics3, and more.\n- All pipeline infrastructure (base class, typedefs, registration pattern, factory function) is in the single file `src/pipelines.js`.\n- The test runner (`collect_and_execute_pipeline_tests`) auto-discovers any file placed in `tests/pipelines/` — no registration needed.\n\n### Changes (2 files, no existing code modified)\n\n**`src/pipelines.js`** — 5 additions:\n1. Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing `import … from './models.js'` block\n2. Add `@typedef` JSDoc block (`ImageTextToTextSingle`, `ImageTextToTextOutput`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineType`) — after the `ImageToTextPipeline` class\n3. Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class — same location, following `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` convention; `_call(image, text, generate_kwargs)` calls `this.processor(image, text)` then `model.generate()`, strips echoed input via the same character-trimming pattern used by `TextGenerationPipeline`\n4. Add `\"image-text-to-text\"` entry to `SUPPORTED_TASKS` (after `\"image-to-text\"`) with `tokenizer`, `pipeline`, `model`, `processor`, `default`, and `type: \"multimodal\"`\n5. Add one JSDoc bullet to the `pipeline()` function's task list\n\n**`tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js`** — new file: instance check + inference output shape check, using a tiny test model.",
